reviews.text: I simply loved this place! with excellent food options this was certainly one of my favorite tours in Barcelona. I had delicious, fresh juices. I had fish dishes and delicious seafood. And what about the ham? wonderful! highly recommended!

Has to be seen its some spot for market fresh food loads of hustle and bustle going on. The smells of the different stalls are amazing. Very good value here. The place is usually thronged with people which some may not like. Nice little bars inside too so something for everyone to sample.

Nice covered market. Fresh products - fresh fruits, fishes, vegetables, seafood. I recommend to try fruit drinks and local bust. The market is full of different colors and odors. The staff is very fast and friendly. Place is really lively. You can really find a lot of interesting things.

Went here for breakfast most mornings.
Now, I don't drink coffee but I drink the espresso here.
Lots of morning and evening snacks here and already cooked.
Just wish we had an apartment and not a hotel room.
I would so love to cook with these fresh ingredients.
Brought home some spices.

Great place where you can find every kind of food, especially fresh fish that you can eat fresh or cooked. Oysters is the best product that you can find there. There are also a lot of stands where you can taste tapas and fresh fruits. Everything is cheap and good. Just one problem: it is close on Sunday!!

I was here a month ago. Took seafood paella. I really enjoyed it! It was one of the best meal I have ever had! And nice atmosphere. In 3 weeks I will arrive in Barcelona again. Can't wait to visit El Glop for the second time :)

This was a wonderful find. The food was delicious,  excellent in proportions and moderately priced. 

The service was phenomenal! I had wondered why every sit down (non-tapas) meal I had opened with toast, tomatoes and garlic. Our server showed our table what to do to make tomato toast. 

Had a very strong family atmosphere.

We went there last sunday, the personnel obviously wanted us to leave as quick as possible to make room for other tourists (very touristic place). I took a mixed grilled meat which was served almost cold. Quality is ok.
Typical Catalan restaurant. Just fabulous. I've been visiting el Glop since 1992 and never been disappointed!
I highly recommend the vegetarian paella. The rice is full of flavor and is topped with roasted vegetables.

Absolutely Fab! Every bite of food that entered my mouth was purely delicious. The kind severs make it their duty to give you 100% satisfaction! If you’re in Barcelona, I highly recommend you go here 😝.

Good value set menu with nice enough food and big portions. 
Nice interiors and staff. 
It's in the guide books and comes recommended but it won't blow ya socks off like.
Service is not bad. Lovely meal. Great ambiance and great service from Michael! We would definitely go back here

Location is great, right on a spectacular square with palm trees and restaurants all around. It's a big place so service is a bit slow. The food was ok, my girlfriend really enjoyed the lamb, my slow cooked pork was alright. Most importantly, a litre of house red was 7.50.

Extremely nice staff, willing to accept customers and serve politely even 10 minutes before close. The second floor is highly recommended for the nice view and wide tables. Prices are absolutely great for the area. Food is of course subjective but personally we enjoyed everything that we ordered.

The music hall is very impressive. I love the sun stained glass ceiling. Also the sculptures on stage are very cool. I'm not a big fan of guided tours (I prefer to explore by myself) so I wish they had an option to check out the place without a tour. But it guide was very friendly and the intro movie was a high production piece. I also wish they would let you walk onstage to get a better view of the statues.

I saw it from outside and decided to force my parents to accompany me to one of the tours - we did not regret it! This concert hall is incredible! It is like stepping into another time. Our tour guide was amazing and we even got a sample of the sound quality. I have to come back for a whole concert at some point.

So beautiful !! The tour guide was nice but the tour itself is a bit boring tho and you can get the same info in booklets and even more in wiki. I'd suggest to spend same amount of money on some concert in the hall so you get some extra experience and time to enjoy the architecture. Its very pretty (and surprisingly small).

What a beautiful venue. The building is worth a visit in itself. We went for a guitar trio and flamenco dancing. There is not a bad seat in the house, any level has a great view. We would definitely go back. I recommend going early and having a drink in the lounge beforehand just to spend more time in the building.

Amazing building and wonderful architecture. The sonority is quite unique, so though visiting the place can be interesting in itself I would recommend staying for a show or concert. The cafe on the ground floor is fine though a little expensive, and can get very busy during the intermission. By the time you get your drink or food, the show will be about to start and you cannot take drinks up to the concert hall. In any case a wonderful building, which is well worth visiting and attending a show in. Also, the loos are clean and modern.

Great place to visit. It is majestic inside. Definitely one of my favorites in Barcelona. A lot of different styles and each room has its personality. It is close to la Boqueria so I would recommend to add this to your list.
Beautiful building, amazing design. The audio guide is a great way to get insights into the design and draw your attention to wee details. Decent price at around €11 when I visited in March 2019.

Fantastic Plaza with historic architecture and of course the Star Gaudi, right outside. The plaza is filled with palm trees, statues, restaurants, Cafe's, and shops. Standing inside is a great experience of the combination of its architectural features and the mix of hustle and bustle. Great place for spending a few minutes or sitting back and enjoying a coffee or meal. Either way it is a must stop over.
Beautiful Gaudi house and a lot cheaper than any of the others. Well worth the visit

A good opportunity to taste Gaudi's architecture.
It closes at 5.30 but they start emptying the floors from 5.10. Make sure to be earlier than 16 in order to have a good time

The cathedral is charming and inspiring. Built in the Gothic style with a monastery. Inside of cathedral you can see fountain and pond, where lives 13 gooses. Inside you can admire the organ and the whole Gothic style. The cathedral is beautiful from the inside and from outside. I recommend to visit, when you are in Barcelona.

On the day that I visited the Cathedral after looking around outside as well as the inside of it, I really like the Gothic Construction and it is well kept.  It is quiet and peaceful so you can enjoy it for as long as you want.  Right outside the Cathedral there is a small plaza and there are events that happen.  This time there was a live band playing and plenty of people joined to dance while listening to the band.  It was a lot of fun, and the church was gathering funds for a cause. It was worth stopping by and much more because of the music and fun.  Stop by if you are near by you will not be disappointed.

A beautiful Cathedral, big inside. You can get in for free on pray hours but you have to be quiet 🤫. There is an elevator that takes you up to the roof with the small amount of 3€ and totally worth it cause you can see a beautiful panoramic view of Barcelona. (if you are scared of highs it's a little bit scary). Don't miss it!

One of the Most Wonderful place in Barcelona. The Cathedral is very Marvellous.Its Beautiful from outside and inside. In summer Its Always Jam packed. Surrounded by some more amazing sites,Restaurants, tapas and Bars. Be Aware of Pickpockets. Easy access from throughout the Barcelona. Bus V15, 45 and 47 pass by. Metro 4 is also an option to get here. Definitely Recommend.

This is a stunning cathedral in the centre of Barcelona. The views from the exterior are amazing as you stand on the street in the sun shine. It is easy to appreciate the magnitude of the architecture here.

The interior is equally beautiful and the inside has a truly gothic feel. There are beautiful paintings and sculptures throughout.

 A small draw back is the candles are electric rather than real which means the atmosphere is not quite the same.

Well worth a visit.

Remnants of the main synagogue of Barcelona. Do not expect an actual synagogue, the Jewish community was forcefully converted in 1391, and it's main sites thoroughly destroyed. 
What remains of Jewish memory in Barcelona is scattered, and easy to overlook.
The hidden gem here are the guided visits the synagogue provides in Spanish, English, Hebrew, etc. They will help you to understand jewish life in medieval Barcelona.
They charge to go in so we didn't get past the front room. Looks cool though.
Worth a visit, €3.50 donation to enter. Quite small but full of fantastic history and staff give short speech on the jewish history and how it links in with Barcelona.

I had the pleasure to photograph a beautiful intimate wedding in the old Synagogue. I loved the atmosphere, the staff was very friendly, all prepared till a small little details for a perfect celebration.

We was not able to find the place on our first visit to Barcelona. It was around midnight in the middle of October - very common time for Barcelona to be out and explore place around. We wanted to find the Ancient Synagogue to be able to come here again at the day time. Interesting to say, at we were not alone, there was another couple trying to find the place - no luck. We returned next year at the day time,  we did it! It was worth the time and money to know the background of the Call carrer (Jewish community location in Barcelona).

It was not bad, but there isn't a lot to see inside. Comparing it to the Paris Erotic museum, this one looked shabby. There were a couple of Picasso originals supposedly, but nothing to write home about. When we entered and were about to get our tickets, the girl at the register called the one in front of the museum to ask her what price she had given us (in Spanish). We hadn't been given a price so she told us, 10 € each. I asked her (in Spanish) I saw a better price online. She ended up saying she would give us a group discount and we paid 7 € each (which I still consider too much for the place but whatever). Learning languages pays off! 

Long story short, it's a fun tourist trap I guess. Maybe have a couple of drinks before you go in and make sure you ask for a discount.

Not bad for a few euro. Some cool information but also seems like they were going for shock factor in a way. The scent tour was something very different and interesting. Check them out. If your not super open minded then this isn't for you.
Absolutely loved it! So many interesting historical facts and things to see. There is a little bit for everyone! (Minus kids of course). Would recommend to anyone visiting

Multiple rooms with different themes all very interesting and educational. Here you will learn a lot about the history of sex leading up to the modern day. I especially enjoyed an interactive display they have in which you can smell different perfumes associated with eroticism. Cost is €10 and you can easily spend an hour here.
Fun and interesting little place. It was very entertaining to see the erotic devices of the past. We had a good time
As stated in other reviews, this is not the hospital but a medieval building. Anyway is nice and worth the visit
Amazing place. I will come here again
Excellent

Història i medicina en la Barcelona gòtica.
Interessant per anar amb joves.

Lugar maravilloso en pleno centro , es cono entrar a otro mundo , puedes tomar algo en alguna de las terracitas ke hay dentro o en disfrutar de la lectura en un ambiente idílico , lástima la cantidad de yonkis aunke le da un toque ke mas vintage...???

Very nice and clean park. Very big, you can plan an entire day trip. A lot of information is written in English. Beautiful surroundings and nice picnic area. I recommend to take snack and drink with you. We saw a lot of different animals. Very interesting. We enjoyed in dolphin show also. From the animal's point of view, this is kind of a prison - restricted area of movement, many visitors. The reality is a little sad, but it is visible that staff is taking care very good for all animals. All praise for this. In the end is very nice souvenir shop.

Really great value for money, we spent over 4 hours here and had the best time. Some bits were closed for refurbishment and I think it will be even better once they are reopened. All the animals had ample space and seemed really well looked after.

Amazing zoo. With large enclosures for the animals, hands on experiences and great swing and slide parks for the kids to burn off some energy. The cafes and restaurants are a little expensive but you can take a picnic with you and there are some great picnic tables situated looking over the enclosures and the animals.

Zoo Barcelona has been a pleasant discovery for me (I don;t like zoos actually)! Quiet, full of old trees and sunny lawns, it's a hermitage for lots of happy animals. The habitats are built with love and common sense. I loved the possibility to see giraffes, kangaroos, various birds, one amazing Komodo dragon and lots of other inhabitants of this wonderful zoo, where you can spend a day like a journey to the world of nature. The place is definitely worth coming back again and again.

One of my favorite places in Barcelona. A must see attraction. Great for families and kids. Tip: bring your snack and water. Also, book your tickets online in advance (I booked mine 2 hours before my visit, and got them on my mobile, scanned them at the gate directly from my mobile, no need for printed tickets). Enjoy
Great location, well priced, basic rooms. However this is not a 4.5 star hotel. Service is patchy and they miss a lot of basics. Not any variety for food. Nice view and rooftop with a small pool.
I spoke with two young ladies on reception, one was Sarah and they were both delightful and extremely helpful and a huge asset to an excellent hotel. Well done!
Excellent hotel! Glad to have spent a few days here, I've enjoyed every minute of it. This would be my choice next time I go to Barcelona.

This hotel is amazing, currently staying here for a 2 night stay, I cannot fault this hotel, they are great. They go above & beyond, the rooms are fab. I would defo recommend this hotel, you will not regret it.
very comfortable room and delicious breakfast. but the WiFi is terrible. you have to reconnect it every 10 minutes.

Molt bonic per passar una estona amb els petits. No és per passar tot el dia. Nens de 4 anys millor el cosmocaixa, no entenen res però s'ho passen molt bé apretant botons i veient com es mouen els experiments. Per no pagar aparcament, aparcar a Diagonal Mar, 3 hores gratis d'aparcament.

We really enjoyed our dinner here. Great service, excellent food, and good prices. Everything on the menu is vegetarian or vegan. We ordered the Aquí Hay Tomate and Magic Burger. Both were very tasty and fresh. I wish we had discovered this spot a bit sooner on our trip!
LOVED IT!! Amazing plant based good, very filling and all delicious. The deco and the staff are also amazing

Meh. I had the set menu at €16 for three courses. The soup was bland and needed salt and pepper to make it palatable. The main I had was a patty of pumpkin and spinach with sauce and rice. I'm not sure I agree that it was pumpkin and though it was more flavorful than the starter, it lacked any texture. Vegetarian and vegan food can be healthy AND amazing tasting. This was maybe one?

Good healthy food.. Combined buffet for lunch.
Place has a good vibe and staff is friendly. 
Would recommend for a chill lunch if you are in the area.

The service is very poor. They forget about your requests and it takes long to get anything. The food is very simple and not tasty (Flax and Kale is much better) . The salad contained of salad, avocado and sour sauce, very bitter and doesn't cost 9 euros. Don't recommend
Poco que aportar. Un chino mas. Sinceramente la comida ni la he probado, pero es que el local no acompaña a ello.
No tiene nada que ver con can conesa de la plaza de san jaume pero los bocatas tambien estan buenos

Genial para tomarte algo con los amigos en una terraza. Nosotros vamos siempre y Xan (el dueño) nos trata de maravilla.
Siempre ponen olivas, cacahuetes, fuet o jamón con cada ronda de bebidas. (puede que el fuet y el jamón nos lo hemos ganado como clientes habituales, no estoy seguro jeje)

El típic bar de tota la vida que l'han comprat uns xinesos i continua sent igual que fa mil anys. Bo, barat, i amb l'al·licient que la terrassa sempre sol tindre lloc disponible i, justament, fa cantonada en un lloc on mai no sol haver-hi gaire afluència de cotxes.
Nice variety of sweets and savoury foods.
Fresh and delicious sweets and bakery products
Delicious and fresh sweets centre in Barcelona 👌👍
Muy buen producto a buen precio, a destacar una especie de Napolitanas de pollo (Picante), que eran riquisimas, y los Baklava geniales, ya he ido a comprar un par de veces, y seguiré viniendo.
La mejor de Barcelona..

This joint isn't upmarket and pretentious. But it does serve up an amazing paella. The chicken was good and similar to what we have back home. The price is affordable and I would certainly come back if I'm in that part of the world again. A paella for two and one quarter chicken cost us 28.50 euro. The staff were happy to serve tourists.

Practically the most authentic local eatery we've tried during our stay in town. You'll get to know new dimensions of quick service at this dirty little place, get a place at the bar downstairs (wait if necessary) where the action is, order the signature quarter chicken with fries, moisture it with a fresh salad and lubricate the whole thing with an ice cold beer. We've paid 10 eur for the whole meal, it's worth every penny.
I ate here twice during my visit, good food and nice coffee. I had the chicken and potato tapas twice and I very much enjoyed their coffee. I like the local atmosphere.
Great food and exceptional customer service. The place it doesn't look nice but the food is amazing, the best I had in Barcelona.

You will never get in, if you don't know the place, since it seems dirty and not clean, but it is definitely one of the best place to eat in Barcelona. Here you can eat a very delicious paella and drink a good sangria for very very cheap. Patatas bravas are among the best I've never eaten. Waiters are wired but kind and nice. I really recommend this place.
Amazing tapas. Great atmosphere. Cool owner. This isn't a huge place, but it's a gem. Love coming here and will be back again.
Had a lovely meal here with such unusual twists to it especially the curry icecream. Will be back for more one day soon.

Good place at the surroundings of La Ramblas. Serves good tapas, altough not the best we've seen in Barcelona. 
Style and athmosphere are trendy and aims for tourists, but its as most places at this area.
Prices are bit high, not too much
Lovely place! Amazing steak, wine and I love the art work.
The food had an interesting twist and was amazing.  We'll definitely be back.

Food was bad and they billed the number of beers wrongly and did not accept their mistake at all. We had only 6 beers but they charged us for 9 beers. We felt cheated at the end. Very expensive and not worth the money.
Food quality was not good. They cheated us by charging us for 9 beers when we had only 6.. we will not suggest this place for others.

When you go in Spain the first thing you think is Paella. That one was terrible. The rice wasn't good and the chicken (we took the chicken one) was full of bones. Carpaccio and patata weren't good for the strange sauces on it.  At least only Sangria was very good. The service was ok and the waiters very polite.

My wife and I were walking on the boardwalk and were approached by a someone trying to bring traffic into the restaurant. I normally avoid the hard sell, but my wife wanted to try fideuà. I was pleasantly surprised - the service was excellent, food was fantastic, and prices were reasonable. (And it’s nice to have a beach view during dinner.) Out of 3 days in Barcelona, this was the friendliest servers and best food we had.

Had the paella and NO complaints on the food. The servers were very friendly and helpful. I gave them 4 stars because it took forever to get our bill. As we were leaving,  we learned they were having card billing issues. Should have told us instead of ignoring us.

Really nice restaurant, had tapas to start and fish for main. Tapas was very nice. The fish however was so well cooked, some of the best I have ever had. Staff were very attentive and we felt well looked after. Definitely recommend

Good restaurant, special thanks to the woman who serve us during the dinner this 29/01/19.
I didn't put 5 stars just because I found that only 2 desserts is too less for the menu. However, everything was good.

This is my all time favourite in Barcelona for more than 10 years. I love their Patatas Bhutan and the rice. Located right on the beach, it is always great to walk around the restaurant after lunch/dinner.

We do follow recommendations and this was definitely one of the best places we have been to. 
Quite place, lovely dinner with great food and superb service. 
We all had different plates and all cooked perfectly and nicely presented. Quantity great and very good price. Good food from start to desert, which is made by their own staff. Ask for wine suggestions.
Food was very good. We ended up here as Cape Diem was fully booked and I was so glad it was as the service here is much more of a higher standard!

I had dinner at Bestial on Friday night. I had 3 glasses of white wine. The first 2 glasses were €4.50. I was charged €18 for the third glass. I brought this to the attention of the server and he did refund me straight away. 

The location is great. The food and wine were very good but I do think they are overpriced.

Great location. I arrived at a busy time but they managed to fit me in. Lots of families having a good time. Had a delicious aubergine soup with poached egg and ham, which I could eat all day, so yummy. Followed at a relaxed schedule by a seafood paella which was equally tasty and filling. Finally had frozen yogurt with blackberry which was sweet, sharp and smooth. A little red wine and coffee rounded off a great visit. Highly recommended.
What we ate was very good and we ate here a second time. Eating outside on Dec. 29 & Dec. 31 was awesome! The view is beautiful looking out into the Mediterranean!

We sat outdoors for dinner, I put my camera bag at my feet. A waiter came to help the order, was oddly moving his body to attract our attention, when we were asking for the password to wifi. After we finished the order, I then realized that my camera bag has been stolen by someone else I haven't noticed. I informed a waitress my situation. She then called the security help checking the video record from surveillance camera. The security described that there was a man sitting on the border of the outdoor platform, on my backside, a short distance from me, pretending to read a map. The man took my camera bag away while we were making the order with the waiter. The security told me, the man has gone, out of Catalonia. The waiter did saw the man, but he never warned me. I never saw the waiter coming to our table again after the incident. I guess that the waiter helped the perpetrator. The restaurant should be responsible for hiring suspected criminal accomplice, hiring useless security and for not warning customer to watch their goods while suspected person is near. A bad dining experience in Barcelona......
I love the mood and view in there. Octopus is great

Went for tapas here because of the great reviews. Food was good but nothing special. Staff were friendly and the experience of sitting at the long bar to eat was fun. However, my advice would be don't eat anywhere that has no menu or display of their prices! One of the reviews said "a little more  pricey than most tapas bars but worth it". We were therefore prepared to pay a little more, but our bill of €101 for 2 people was a little hard to swallow!! We had 7 plates and drinks. Drinks were very good value but one of the plates was €17 for a sausage with beans in wine sauce! One plate was €19.99 and we're not even sure what it was! Best of all we had a lovely tapas the day before for about €33 for 6 plates and drinks.

Food is excellent. Highly recommend the seafood. Tapas plates here are slightly larger than most places. Three dishes (two veggie and one fish) is plenty for one person. Sangria is nice as well. The restaurant definitely lives up to expectations.

I hate this restaurant. It has literally ruined all other food for me for the rest of my life. The price is a bit steep but so worth it. 

This place looks a bit like a typically sit at the counter dinner. But when you go in there is no menu to look at. The server will recommend multiple tapas plates. Say yes to anything he suggests, he knows what he's talking about. Seriously. I had an omelette and I don't think I'll ever taste anything as delicious again in my life. The food is great quality, comes out quickly, the atmosphere is laid back, it's the perfect restaurant.

As great as expected.  Went in January, so not massively busy.  Fabulous ambience at the (non-reservable) counter tops.  

Great friendly, enthusiastic service.  The tailored food came out at a perfect rate, with explanations.  Focus on seafood.  Clams amazing.  The tortilla was the best I’ve ever eaten.  It’s clear they’ve tried to keep the focus on quality yet simply made food they are used to.   

I’ll come here every time I visit Barcelona.
Well worth the queue in. Sit at the bar and let the waiter order his recommendations. Beautiful and unique feed. A little pricier than some of the cheap tapas bars but definitely worth the visit.

Wonderful place for calçotada and I'm pretty sure that during other time they have awesome service and food. Staff to protect yourself when eating calçots is very useful, as you keep hands clean and protected from sauce. They have quite big wine choice. Definitely, I'll come here one more time.

Beer good with a black rice pallea, 
Pork chop, salad with tomato and union, kambas, etc.
5 stars for the staff, ZERO for the food, not delicious, and texting this while recovering from mild poisoning! I wish there was a zero star rating!

We had the BEST time here, enjoying a true calçotada! It was great because one of us ordered the calçotada menu and then the other just ordered an entree, so the price was great, and we had plenty of food to enjoy. The staff was fantastic, being so helpful and patient with our broken Spanish and very generous. The food was delicious!! We really couldn’t have had a better time here. I’d highly recommend eating here, especially in the winter for calçot season, and if you aren’t sure what that is, just go and order them, you will not be disappointed. We can’t wait to return!
Server at the outside was so friendly also good at english!! Taste of food was really nice 👍👍
This place is a must visit in Barcelona. Such a great atmosphere. Lively, fun. Great food, service. Amazing smells from the kitchen. Get here.

Restaurant established in 1835. Outdoor charcoal rostisserie built into the outside corner of the building!!!! Smelled so good outside we changed our plans and when in. Tiny hole in the wall place. Thought it was just a bar until we got brave enough to walk through to the underground area that was the restaurant! Turns out to be two stories and hidden rooms up and down stairs. Very fun. Waiters were just the right amount of attentive and happy to help or make recommendations of you need it, in any language.  Menu is in at least 5 languages. Excellent food and wine options. So great to walk through the very hot kitchen to get to the eating areas. We started with creamy asparagus soup with Ham, and steamed Mussels, then the roasted chicken dinner and King Prawns. Finished with creme brulee and a cappuccino. Delicious! Will go again!

We decided to go here on a whim, based off reviews here. 
At first we thought we had the wrong place, as it just looked like a small bar, but we were soon led through the kitchen itself which was a cool touch, and through dining rooms and past an active well.

The cured ham hanging from the ceiling, the winding stairs and autographed celebrity photos on the walls all gave the place a unique and fascinating charm, it was like stepping back in time (the restaurant opened in 1835).

We heard the chicken was to die for and was what Los Caracoles was famous for, which made it doubly strange that they had ran out of roast chicken for my partner, but could still serve me the garlic chicken... I don't understand how.

Service was fine, nothing to gush or complain about, and the food itself was really nice, although portions were a tad small for the prices. 

Overall it was an amazing and interesting experience, but as a meal it was average.

I would probably give Los Caracoles 3 stars if it weren't for the great service. What I thought would be a small bar with some tables turned out to be a huge restaurant! We walked through the kitchen into room after room, not believing how big the place is. There is even a second floor! The servers were all so great, making recommendations, explaining the menu, and being friendly and polite. We ordered the entrecote steak and half chicken. I think the chicken came from the rotisserie that you can see outside, but I'm not sure. The steak was a little undercooked, very salty, and fairly fatty. The fries on the side were fine. The rotisserie chicken was a bit dry, also salty, but not bad. The potatoes that came with it were also fine, but nothing special. We were charged for 2 breads 3.98€ that we didn't order or receive, so they took that off the bill. The food overall wasn't bad, just not worth what they charge for it. They do have some really cool photos on the walls. The feel of the restaurant is great, with a lot of charm. Kind of old school, like everyone is part of something there.  Again, the service was wonderful though. I might stop back again when they are serving tapas.

If I’m not mistaken, this is the oldest restaurant in Barcelona, or one of the oldest(working since 1835). Fantastic place! The biggest cultural experience I’ve ever had in a restaurant. The interior is great, the staff is great, service is on point. Food(national Catalan cuisine)is beyond any description - delicious, to say the least. Pricey, but for that quality I reckon you would pay exactly that. Definitely would recommend visiting ‘Los Caracoles’ yourself to feel that unique atmosphere. 10/5!

Platos pequeños,cenas informales y posibilidad de probar sabores distintos.Su local es pequeño,a dos alturas,rustico,simpaico y con mucha imaginacion.
Comida de mercado internacional,pinchos,cazuelitas con especialidades arabes,griegas o japonesas,como kefte con cuscus,atun macerado con aceite de oliva y soja,pollo macerado es especias,cordero a la griega o ceviche de pescado.
Los postres sencillos,quesos,helados o tarta casera.Ambiente muy informal.
The best staff on the world. If you become homeless, go there, they will sincerely help you.
Great Service
Nice
A charity assisting homeless people. Among other functions they collect second hand clothes and shoes, which they distribute on request on spot. Only male clothes are accepted.
Amazing

So disappointed. It had been on our list since we saw the place during a walking tour. Extremely slow and sloppy service and terrible food. Got some tiny mussels that were old and rubbery. Even the bread was bland. Such a shame because it’s a beautiful place with great potential and some interesting history.
The place is i credibly beautiful. It is really an experience to sit there. But thier cocktails where pretty basic, the staff was snobby. This is a place i would just go once to see the architecture.

Great jazzy vibe in a gorgeous part of the city with a casual aire of timeless intellectuality. Decent cortados, better cafe con leches. Would recommend for those looking to share the tastes that inspired the great artists of Barcelona.

This is our second visit to this restaurant 

We were so impressed about our first visit in March 2018, prices were fair and services was excellent, that was reason we decided to visit again In early January 2019.

This time we do felt the food were fair, menu changed, we simply took the recommendations from the staff and did not aware about the prices which was in fact increased nearly 20%, frankly speaking for the first time visitors surely not aware of this, as we all were cheated by the historical side of this restaurant, and not realize the cost are escalating while the quality are dropping (see the previous comments on Google, people had the  same issue we experienced).

They charged the bread @ €3.18 per person also unreasonable !

Sorry this will be the last visit to this restaurant and sad to see the deterioration of their reputation !

Meantime on this trip we found plentiful of new and good restaurants in Barcelona, so there are so much choices for tourists, do hope the 4 Cats restaurant management do see the seriousness to rectify the situation.
This was my second time here. The food is great but you have to pay for the experience

Very good restaurant for Spanish food. Vast variety of paella, sweet environment and professional staff. Not cheap but high quality. Very recommend.

I returned here on Valentine’s Day of 2019. I reserved a table and brought a cake. Surprisingly each table has been offered Cava and my cake was put a candle. So sweet staff and I decided to share the entire cake with the staff :)

Apparently the restaurant listened to earlier complaints about the food being too salty, as my food had no seasonings whatsoever and there was no salt or pepper on the table or any table in sight. My veal fillet was dry and boring and my fries were 'seasoned' with suspicious crunchy pieces of some other meat, probably leftover in the oil. Presentation was meh, and overall experience very disappointing.
Nice paella but waiters are kind of rude and they don’t have enough stuff. It’s almost difficult to get the waiter to attend you
The food was too salty and almost inedible. Staff should be more friendly to foreigners. Place looks cozy though.
The place looks cozy inside. But the waiter was careless to us. The Paella was too salty for my taste and way too expensive for what was actually worth it.

Food was nice but the chicken was under cooked.

Quaint & ecclectic.  Food was average, not fond of the horse-raddish ice cream.  Friendly staff but a bit pricey (no different than the rest of Barcelona).  I don't think I will return but wouldn't "not" recommend it.  Try it if you want.

We had to wait quite a bit, even if it wasn't really filled, but my grilled tuna with mushed celery was really good, we loved the recommended wine and all three of us enjoyed the stay. The cheesecake was a great dessert. Maybe not the cheapest place.
Very elegant place, very Friendly waiters and very fairly priced. The food is also very yummy, try the gnocchi!

Good Service. And very good Mojitos. Me and my freinds felt very comfortable. The location has very good vibes.
Greets from Germany :)

Great entertainment in making our meal. Very accommodating for vegans.  And picky eaters (me).  Downside, long time on your feet - market visit and the cooking area. But all the ups far out weigh that one item. Great double cooked fries.

Had a great gastronomy cooking class on June 21.  Took my wife and 2 kids and the instructor kept the whole family engaged and entertained.  Plus, the class was educational and the food was tasty.  I would highly recommend.

Great learning experience on how to cook paella, gazpacho, starters and Catalan cream desert. Included a market tour with tastings of signature Spanish foods. Small group of students and a very knowledgeable chef. A beautiful kitchen and a great experience.

Our family had an amazing experience here to celebrate my birthday.  We were completely engaged from the first minute we arrived and the chef and staff were kind and gracious.  It is a beautiful space too.  It was  an excellent "class" but  it was also an exceptional way to work together in an unusual activity we loved it, and the food, was wonderful.  Best meal in Barcelona for me.   Now all I want is to try it on my own!
We had a great experience at our cooking class here. The space is beautiful, food is delicious, and the staff was great with our four year old. Highly recommended!

Cheap and cheerful place, but the pizza quality is bad (base is not good and the toppings are very cheap). Air conditioning doesn’t really work most of the time and toilets are not very clean... I could go on but just avoid this dingy place unless it’s the only thing opened...
una pizza ecelent i un magnific serbei
A good place to go if you want a decent and cheap pizza. The beer is a little pricey.
I had a great time eating pizza here! It is a must have in Spain!
Local thin pizza, almost always open

We were visiting the Castell And were advised to visit 7 Ported.
We didn't bring fine clothes but felt we should have while eating here.
Well trained staff with professional service.
White table cloths and good that tells you it was prepared by a chef. Excellent moment.

Been here several times in the past 10 years. Never disappoints. Some of the best Paella in Barcelona. Also very good steak options. Great for business dinners with a high-end atmosphere. Reservations available online, large parties require a deposit.
A very good traditional Catalan restaurant.  Very smart and efficient service. Great range of tapas although the paella somewhat disappointing.  The specials are very good

Beautiful, historic restaurant with excellent service and an optimal location. The food is well made and flavorful, but be aware that the prices reflect the craftsmanship and the renowned reputation the restaurant exhibits. The portions are not big, as is customary with this kind of establishment and there is still some mark up since this is a big tourist destination. You can expect to have a very pleasant experience and eat some very yummy food. 

Overall, I would recommend it if it is within your budget. If it is not however or if you just don't want to pay this much for dinner, I don't want you to think you're missing out on some one of kind dining experience. It's entirely possible to get super delicious food at better prices in the city.

#1: make a reservation, I'm so glad we did because there were at least 40 people outside just waiting for them to open. They don't overbook or crowd the diners, so it was lovely and peaceful inside

#2 seafood paella was delicious- perfectly cooked and seasoned

#3 they charge for the olives and bread they bring to the table- €2.40. This is a very common practice- if you don't want it and don't want to be charged,  don't eat it. You will miss out on dipping your bread into the paella pan though

I simply loved this place! with excellent food options this was certainly one of my favorite tours in Barcelona. I had delicious, fresh juices. I had fish dishes and delicious seafood. And what about the ham? wonderful! highly recommended!

Has to be seen its some spot for market fresh food loads of hustle and bustle going on. The smells of the different stalls are amazing. Very good value here. The place is usually thronged with people which some may not like. Nice little bars inside too so something for everyone to sample.

Nice covered market. Fresh products - fresh fruits, fishes, vegetables, seafood. I recommend to try fruit drinks and local bust. The market is full of different colors and odors. The staff is very fast and friendly. Place is really lively. You can really find a lot of interesting things.

Went here for breakfast most mornings.
Now, I don't drink coffee but I drink the espresso here.
Lots of morning and evening snacks here and already cooked.
Just wish we had an apartment and not a hotel room.
I would so love to cook with these fresh ingredients.
Brought home some spices.

Great place where you can find every kind of food, especially fresh fish that you can eat fresh or cooked. Oysters is the best product that you can find there. There are also a lot of stands where you can taste tapas and fresh fruits. Everything is cheap and good. Just one problem: it is close on Sunday!!

The apartments are quite beautiful. The audio guide was very informative. Had a great time but I have seen more spectacular buildings before. I think beautiful and aesthetics are very subjective so please read my review with a pinch of salt.
Great stop and tour of building. Attic is incredible to see. Plan for at least a 1 to 1.5 hr visit. Loads of great photo opportunities. Don't miss a visit here.

Wonderful experience. The roof is fantastic and view from it amazing. The exhibition room is impressive. Amazing Gaudi's architecture, wonderful details. Chimneys like sculptures, iron work on the doors and balconies is wonderful. I fully recommend to visit. To see everything you need at least two hours.

So glad we came and visit. Awesome, place, great experience. (even my 12 yr old nephew thoroughly enjoyed it who categorically said before hand that he is not interested and going to dislike it. It was full entertainment for him) Our slot was a mid morning one which also was very pleasant, not too crowded (in March at least)  Helpful staff, great shops. Really was worth it! Highly recommended.
Wonderful experience. The roof is fantastic and view from it amazing. The exhibition room is impressive. Amazing Gaudi's architecture, wonderful details. I fully recommend to visit.

I loved this tour. The tour guide spoke perfect English, which was wonderful because my Spanish is purely light conversation. The rooms are so elegant and beautiful, and such gorgeous woodwork and detail is to be found everywhere. The tour is thorough, and it finishes in the chocolate shop where you can purchase some delicious souvenirs. A must see!

This is not so noticeble if you aren't looking for it. But location is easily accessible with a metro stop just in front of it. A small area in the ground floor is open for free access. Could get some interior view from there. Inside has some beautiful staircase and lamps with intricate work.
It was beautiful but full of tourists and their guides.
I thought it was Gaudi, but it was not. Even them, it is very nice.
Just visited the store.  Good chocolates to bring back as gifts.
Amazing place to see, best 8 euro I've spent in Barcelona!

I was here for an event within the foundation multiple times, so I can only speak to what I saw in passing to the conference room at the back. The space within is interesting and inspiring. The content, while at first seems ñ bland and uninteresting,is quite interesting when you get the story behind the works.
Did know a thing about him... Went out with deep admiration!
Good place to visit if you're into modem art. Even if you don't like much abstract art, it's a great place to understand a bit of the Franc's period in Spain.

Nice, tranquil spot in the heart of Eixample. The outside of the museum is the best. Inside I liked Tapies' art. He does a lot of pieces on a grand scale. Reminded me a little bit of Miró. There's also currently a neat exhibition downstairs from a Turkish artist who drew my attention to a refugee crisis I was unaware of.

But I was grateful that as a local teacher I got in for free. For 7 euros I may not have been as enthralled.

Somewhat of a city centre. Pl. De Catalunya is a big square connecting major roads. Filled with shopping complexes, restaurants and bars this place also has a large open space in the middle usually full of birds. There is a fountain, park benches and there was a stage being set up for some show that weekend. Accessible by bus, metro.
Also a stop for changing lines on the Tourist bus.

It's the main city centre of Barcelona, it's very lively during day time even in the evening. There small restaurant nearby to it. Big brands stores, it's all called as tourist attraction.  We had a great time over here

It's a typical European Square. Very spacious. Elegant and rich in history.Look out for the pigeons and guys selling useless junk like umbrellas and dead battery chargers and other cheap trinkets...pro tip brush up on your Catalan.

Huge place with many lot of people around. They have art and music everywhere in the city but this area is the centre and everything passes from here. There are many fashion brands here on the shopping street, lots of fresh selection on every brand and I just LOVE shopping here. This is very central and very well connected with public transport or many bike sharing stand. They have local coffee places everywhere around which is very nice and fresh

Great plaza in the city center of Barcelona. Placa de Catalunya was filled with people fresh air and lots of birds. This is a great place to stop and relax. You can watch the locals as they go about their day. It's great for people watching. When you leave there are plenty of food options around.

I have a straightforward idea: I come to a restaurant in order to eat the foods that I cannot readily buy from a supermarket. 

Unfortunately, the food here was super generic. Absolutely nothing creative, nothing special, nothing memorable. There are much more in Vegan world than cabbage, lettuce, lentil or pasta.
There is nothing sign about creativity here. Nothing to remember.

Suggestion for the management: be creative. Look at Vegan receipts and prepare some delicious food. I can cook a bowl of lentils at home. I want something new, something by which I remember your restaurant later
I went for a Saturday lunch on my own. The salad/food buffet was very well stocked. And the food was really nice and fresh. For 13 Euros it was definitely a bargain.
I work nearby and It’s good there’s a vegetarian restaurant in this area. It’s a shame its Chef’s creativity falls short in bringing people this far... a 3 min walk
Good selection of salads, some pasta and soup. Great value.
Great! Healthy, delicious food!

It's an all you can eat buffet where you can eat as much as you want for around 11€. First, you create a salad. There are many ingredients and one can make a pretty decent one. Then you fill up a glass with any drink you want there and then you pay. After that there is a food section where there are a few kinds of food. When we were there it was a meat stew, pizza, some kind of pasta, paella and side dishes. Also there are some desserts like ice cream. Food was not bad although it could have been better. If you are hungry and around Sagrada Familia and on a budget then go to this place.

I like this place! Tasty! 

Good place to have a dinner with your friends.

For about 11 euros you can eat well if you are very hungry. This place will be too expensive if you want to drink only a cup of coffee. There is a big assortment of salads, not all delicious, but there are good ones. There are soups, you can take pizza, pasta, chicken, drinks, pay for everything, and then if you do not eat enough you can return and take as much as you want. There's a toilet upstairs, but I did not see an elevator or a toilet for people with disabilities. Therefore, this restaurant is not for everyone.
Really good value for money. Lots of salad, pizza, pasta, chicken and more, plus soft drinks and coffee. Nice and clean too.
Very good and quite place to eat near Sagrada Familia. Clean, friendly, a lot of choice, deserts, fruits and excellent cortado - all you can eat for 11 euros! Highly recommend!

All you can eat for about 10 euros. If you are really hungry this is the right place for you. The food is pretty good. You can choose from salads, pizza, pasta, paella, and more. They had delicious gazpacho when I was there. Some basic drinks are included, so you can drink as much as you want. This place is totally worth it.

Visited the restaurant with work colleagues; 1 Polish/German, 1 French, 1 Argentinian/American and one Lebanese/American. We all loved the food and the atmosphere. We ordered a bunch of tapas to share and they were all very good with no exception. We ordered a nice white wine to go with meal. We also had great desserts, coffee and digestives. Not sure what the negative reviews are all about. I definitely recommend this restaurant.
Clean. Functional. Pleasant staff. Tasty tapas. Reasonably priced.Good service.

The worst meal I've ever had in Spain. Food is not good. They don't even look good. Price is way too much for the amount and quality of the food. At that price you would expect a much better experience. You don't get satisfaction in any aspect.

Liked this place. Paella and sangria were tasty. Officiants are smiley and affable. Costs are not high but portions not very big too.
Nice place to have a break and continue your walking by Barcelona.

Stay away!! Terrible and inattentive wait service except for one young friendly and personable bus person who filled in while the awful server thankfully went for a break.  Many mistakes including being blamed for 'changing mind' when the wrong dish was presented and being charged for a dish that never appeared.

Food was mediocre to passable and not cheap, given the location, and was in fact priced too high for what we received.  We are happy to pay well for exceptional service and tasty dishes, but money spent at Qu Qu today was money wasted.

I am very satisfied with this restaurant! The food is delicious and superb quality! The staff is very friendly and smiling!!! (which is not always the case in other places in Barcelona).
The atmosphere of the restaurant is pleasant.
I can only recommend this superb restaurant!
Nice experience and more space for groups
Food was ok but the service was wavering between unpleasant and bad mannered. Pity. We won't be going back.
Best service, amazing food and good-value menu of the day. I loved the local atmosphere. It is nothing like touristy... It is very authentic!
fantastic food . 4 of us all had different meals. all excellent.  highly recommend this restaurant
Excellent food, good wine, friendly and professional personnel. Strongly recommended.
Service was very slow, waited 30 min for a veggie roll. Good atmosphere, but need to pay more attention about service. Nobody asked me how was my meal or came to ask if I want anything else
Came here for lunch. Had a nice set menu. Good food and service.

Really great spot for a quick brunch! I think it’s better than the famous Brunch&Cake. The food is not that sophisticated, but it really does taste amazing! We had some toast with scrambled eggs and an amazing burger with steak. Also, the menu is much larger :). Definitely worth a try, the brunch is really good and the staff are helpful!
Really very good food and friendly staff. We had the organic braised veg, hummus and fried squid and all was really good. Wine list is also excellent!
Pleasant little creperie. Nice dinner and service. Just hit the spot for us.
Amazing crepes (sweet and salty). Good place for dinner and supper. The service was amazing and so kind!!! Recommended 100%
The best crepes I’ve had in Barcelona. Feels like being in France! :)
Excellent service, great food and great sidra.
Top

I made reservations for my birthday and had a friend also make reservations (there were nine of us and their max is 8). Both of our reservations were confirmed yet when we arrived the restaurant was closed and there was a sign saying they were closed temporarily until Monday. It was a Tuesday and there was no date listed on the sign. Completely ruined the evening (my birthday to be specific). If they are gonna be closed at least put it on the website or don’t TAKE RESERVATIONS.
The food was good, the staff made suggestions for a tourist with no idea what to get in a foreign country. The tequila was good and got my night start well.

The place was rather abandoned on a weekday night, though we're not sure why as the food was pretty good. Not tons of vegetarian options on the menu, but enough for us; lots of options for meat-eaters. We ordered the nachos bravos which were VERY good, and the enfrijoladas which were also tasty. The portions were a bit on the small side, which was too bad.
Awesome food! Best Mexican food I‘ve had in a long time. Great and friendly service too! Highly recommended!
Margarita frozen mmmmm genial idea

We had our work Christmas dinner here.  A beautiful restaurant with a very varied menu. Our group chose a selection of starters to share and all of them were delicious.  I know everyone were happy with the main courses.  The waiters were great offering recommendations with food and wine.
Upstairs they have a cool bar for after dinner cocktails.

We could not recommend this place enough! Came here on the last night of our trip with my partner and it was by far the highlight, the perfect way to top off an incredible vacation. The service was incredible - they were so fast, efficient but really kind and welcoming. The food was from another planet! We had the croquet and cod fritters as starters, which were immaculate. I had the veal and it was cooked to perfection as was my partners Ox Sirloin. Next time we are in Barcelona we will definitely be coming back. Thank you to Mario for making us feel so welcome!

Very good tapas/starter. Our group of 8 had beef/steak cooked on a hot stone. It was excellent. Wine was good too. Didn't get desserts. Too full by then. Dinner was 2.5 hrs long which is typical for Barcelona restaurants.

I was completely shocked at how this place ends up being a trap. We did not ask for starters, but we were charged € 3 for the piece of bread that the waiter put on the plate (and we did not eat it as it was hard). But the worst was yet to come, as we asked what the maitre d 's suggestion was for dinner, and he offered a baked fish with accompaniments. The fish was a flatfish for
Two, without any seasoning (we asked for salt, pepper and olive oil) with a potato that did not know if it was stirred or puree, and only. The price of the dish? 65 € !!!!! An absurd because not even worthy! We spent 127 € with a bottle of white wine, and I have never regretted so much of having gone to a restaurant! It was the waiters completely unprepared, confused ... a horrible experience, which made us spend money idly, in a place that wants to be something, but has no quality to offer.
So elegant, nice staff and goog chioces
Good food and excellent service.

I have had lovely upscale dining experiences before but this was my first Michelin star locale. Food was solid, but not mind-blowing. Service was a bit wonky - they didn't seem glad we were there when we arrived, and no one said goodbye. Our glasses were often empty. No one told us what the desserts were - however, they were the most exceptionally good part of the meal. We decided to have an extremely classy (read: clearly it's expensive, it has a Michelin star) dinner - but we didn't expect to be treated so oddly. The sommelier was the nicest guy, but had a strange tinge to his breathe (and was close enough for me to smell it). I did leave full, and sated - just a little befuddled by the whole experience.

We were sat three to an 8-top table - we were sitting as far apart as if we had to shout to hear each other - but it was eerily quiet in the restaurant and the vibe was just very solemn.

We had fun as friends out to fancy dinner, but not one of us felt this was superb or outstanding service or food. You'll pay 3x what you would at any other restaurant and may also find it to be a bit stiff and awkward.
Nice not overly posh restaurant

If you are expecting amazing food experience, you might be dissapointed. I know better places in Barcelona with better food and service at much lower price. Here you might be lucky but... it can be at best averange as well. Very uneven level of the dishes and my tuna was a big dissapointment. Also service was rather averange. Young was not what you will expect in 1MS restaurant.

Good service but not worth the price at all. We took the traditional tasting menu which was ok, not anything new or mindblowing, flavors were very muddled. We were in way better non michelin restaurants in Barcelona. Would definitely recommend to search for others rather than over priced old fashion Michelin star restaurants.

You do not want to miss this “must see” popular destination of Barcelona! It’s such a beautiful place to witness so many different things from architecture to different plants and the view of Barcelona! It’s also got a lot of stairs so you can expect a nice hike or walk depending on how rigorous you want to to use your energy!

A "must see" in Barcelona! 😍 It's so beautiful.  Amazed by its well designed with thoughtfulness!  Friendly and helpful staff.  The park is easily accessible by bus.  Recommend joining the official guided tour (Euro 15.5).
It will amaze you the amount of time spent in decorating these beautiful place. I wish they could have light effects at night so that the glass designs can shine. It is lovely.
Beautiful place, "must see" in Barcelona.. Make sure you book in advance because it gets really busy and tickets get sold easily. You can still enjoy the park and surrounding area.

I visited the Museum and thought this ticket got me into all of the park ... not so.   Make certain that if you want to visit the main works at this place that you purchase tickets online and at least 2 days in advance as they were sold out.   It still is an enjoyable park to walk through.

Gaudí house museum is just a short walk from the entrance. Rooms have been restored to display Gaudí’s life with his niece and father as he helped to build the park. Just 5.50€ the grounds are beautiful as well as being able to see into the artist home and some of his creations.
It is hill full of Gaudi's buildings. It is awesome view. You can see during nice days   while Barcelona.  Usd bus 24 or Metro. It us quite long way from center of city.
Amazing artist! But the interior inside his house is so humble! Lovely museum and well worth the money :)
Gaudí life... Good place. But there are other places in the city better if you have to chose.

There're some interesting furniture made by him. Apart from the bedroom, which only have a bed and wardrobe, the place is like a museum but not kept as his house. It would be nice to see what the functions of each room and kept the furniture. Anyway, worth a visit if you want to learn about Gaudi.

It's a really good House. Shows the midernistic style of Gaudí in it's core beginning. The first layers are displays of what the house looked like before the renovations and the top layer is for the history of it. The staff and volunteers are really good and helpful. In general I think it's a good place to visit if you only gave one day in Barcelona,  it represents all of it.

Little known, hidden gem of a mansion, the very first house that Gaudí built.
In it, one can already discern the elements that would later define his characteristic style and will turn him to the artist he was to become.
The house, set in a beautiful garden, is a celebration of earthen colors, motives of nature and Sub-Saharan influences.
In the courtyard there is nice café and also a nice souvenir shop.
Very helpful staff, speaking English and eager to point out to you the interesting details.

A hidden and more secret gem of Gaudi's. A little different to his other stuff, and the best part... currently less touristy. 
The tour is very informative. I really enjoyed that. The guide was lovely and she was able to go with the flow, it wasn't all so rehearsed.

Yet another outstanding example of the genius within Gaudí. This is not one of his most famous works, so there usually aren't many crowds, but the building itself is a true work of art. No matter if you enter or if you're just looking from outside, Casa Vicens sure won't ley anyone down.

Gaudi's first house where you can see a lot of the design elements and themes that will be repeated in his other projects. This house was opened to public in Nov of 2017. The guided tour provided a lot of good information.

Not a vegan myself but I am looking into it now. Thought this was a great way to try out some dishes I wouldn't normally order. They also have some vegetarian stuff but the Flavour of the food is good. Starters where nice and the curries were also good!

Hands down the best Indian restaurant in Barcelona. Everything about this place is perfect. From the food to the ambience to the decoration to hygiene to customer service. I would strongly recommend all Indian food lovers to visit this place.

It used to be a cozy restaurant but now is huge and chaotic. Too loud and the staff has not increased so last time we had to wait a lot for them to serve the food... Our reservation was at 21:30h and the food came at 22:45h...

At least, the food quality had not changed, it is so so so good! Very tasty!

Price vs quality is fine!

Friendly staff and even though the food on first sight doesn't look like it but it is very delicious. The whole menu is vegetarian and there are also suitable vegan options.
Reasonable prices!
Loved this place! The midday menu was really tasty, filling and reasonably priced. The waiters were super cool too

Great Lebanese food, the closest to that of Lebanon I've tried so far. Good service and ambiance although the music can be more Lebanese. The staff is very welcoming and helpful and above all, they serve "Almaza", the Lebanese beer
Fantastic place, simple and straightforward interior. Had great service, who recommended beautiful dishes. They had an amazing lunch menu, will definitely visit again.
It was an amazing experience. The food tastes delicious and satisfies your taste buds. At the end you will feel stuffed. Good atmosphere.
The yummiest Lebanese food  in Barcelona ! Highly recommended 👍🏻👍🏻
Food wasn't bad, but it's kind of expensive for what it has to offer. Specially since we had to wait a lot , service was super slow. I've eaten way better food considering the price.
Bar familiar bien atendido
Buen lugar para ir a tomarse unas cervezas y probar las patatas bravas y bocadillos!! 👌🏻

I was here a month ago. Took seafood paella. I really enjoyed it! It was one of the best meal I have ever had! And nice atmosphere. In 3 weeks I will arrive in Barcelona again. Can't wait to visit El Glop for the second time :)

This was a wonderful find. The food was delicious,  excellent in proportions and moderately priced. 

The service was phenomenal! I had wondered why every sit down (non-tapas) meal I had opened with toast, tomatoes and garlic. Our server showed our table what to do to make tomato toast. 

Had a very strong family atmosphere.

We went there last sunday, the personnel obviously wanted us to leave as quick as possible to make room for other tourists (very touristic place). I took a mixed grilled meat which was served almost cold. Quality is ok.
Typical Catalan restaurant. Just fabulous. I've been visiting el Glop since 1992 and never been disappointed!
I highly recommend the vegetarian paella. The rice is full of flavor and is topped with roasted vegetables.

Luxury ambience and interior decoration. The food is perfect and waiters know the menu inside out and are very hospitable. They even indulged us with dishes not on the menu. 
We had the famous fresh tomato paste on crispy fresh bread.
We had a lobster salad to begin with which was very good. Then we had the typical fried calamari which was also made to perfection. Then we had the grilled shrimps with garlic which was just perfect.
The lobster was the main attraction. We had two full lobsters weighing a total 3.3kg (for 3 people). The lobster was super delicious. We then split a paella dish which also came with lobster, which we thought was an overkill. We also had a dish of sauted potato with onion and tomato which was excellent. 
I only gave a 4 star rating because we felt the waiter let us order more lobster than we should and because the waiter from the night before said the meat served was halal whereas our waiter tonight said it wasn't.

What a great place!!! Like travelling back in time. Interior and staff, amazing. Service, top notch. The food is top of the line. Great portions and taste wonderful. Really really worth every penny! In my opinion, not expensive for the amazing quality and amount you get.

The food was good, service was good, and the restaurant is nice. However I only gave it a 4 star since I felt it was way overpriced for what we had. We ordered crab salad, grilled prawns, hams, and paella for 2 people. We ended up paying 100 euro each.
Incredibly tasty. One of the best seafood platters I've ever had. It is a bit pricey but very much worth it

Wonderful food, atmosphere and decor. Our party was seated upstairs and served an array of food that was simply spectacular. The seafood salad, octopus, lobster paella was plentiful and of the highest quality.

Good food.  Missing some salt and cohisvness to be great.  Except for so dashi in the fish course and sesame in the dessert, there is no Japanese connection at all. 
 Service was very friendly but a bit slow, most of the dishes came out lukewarm. 
Ambiance was of a doctor's waiting room.
Catalan regional cuisine, re-invented by a chef who brings in culinary elements of his native Japan, great wines at affordable prices, a charming and competent service team - in brief: a discovery!

Amazing food for a really good price - 18.80 euros for a 3-course lunch set that included free-flow bread, water, tea, beer/wine, appetiser (salmon croquette + cod fish), main (chicken confit), and dessert (cream/apple sorbet). A very memorable meal that was made even better by the very good service

We spent 2 and a half hours eating the "Menu Somodo" (35€) that was really amazing (pictures of everything that is included). Hard to choose the best part of the dinner. You must make a reservation before coming (in their website) because it's a small place. I wish service could be a bit faster (not sure if it is a complaint because maybe you could feel "full" before you are finished), so maybe they could open a bit earlier (opens at 9pm). Anyway, it was a wonderful experience and we were all delighted with the food.

I wouldn't be surprised if they were close to get their first Michelin state. Awesome tasting menu at very affordable price. Not a surprising menu with unknown flavors but extraordinary quality and  enjoying menu. Love the oister and the meat. They can improve on the temperature of the dinning room and maybe increase the wine list. Otherwise it's incredible for the price. Service was super kind and we could not ask for better. Looking forward to come back again to taste another tasting menu as two seems too little for such a nice place.
Great little bar. Popped in there late on out first night in Barcelona mid February. Nice relaxed atmosphere, & the drinks well priced. Would go again.
very well located in gracia, super friendly stuff, delicious tapas and good drinks :) We'll be back!

Had 6 days in Barcelona and visited this bar 4 times , both during the day and in the evening. Tapas was good . Very popular insomuch as we queued for a table on 3 occasions. I don't do that very often as there are plenty of bars. This bar is in a plaza so you have plenty of people to watch. Really enjoyed it.
Good service, lovely location to sit outside. Food and sangria was nice especially the goat cheese salad!
Amazing! Food and staff
Great value admission price of €5 to see the Velasquez exhibition. Beautiful building. Good value lunch with wine in the restaurant although service was initially shabby 🙁

Always interesting exhibitions. The building itself is free to explore and fascinating. The cafe has been renovated - a bit tastelessly, the previous version was much better - but the lunch menus are still excellent, well-priced and imaginative.

Especially good for the return Barcelona visitor or to relax from the other, overcrowded sites.
Went to their Velazquez & Toulouse-Lautrec exhibitions. These were well-balanced, not overstuffed, as can be the case elsewhere I Europe. 
They always have interesting temporary shows that might be overlooked by the usual visitor to Barcelona. 
The location is kind of odd, but nearby is Plaza España and a weird shopping center, The Arena, actually a converted old bullring. 
There are audioguides for the exhibitions which are in various languages and these are very informative. Of course, the staff here, I imagine, speak English.
Nice exhibits, small but accurate. Great option to spend an afternoon and get out of the coach 🙂

The Velazquez exposition was really interesting even though our guide had another guidance so she was rushing to finish it and go to the other one. The painting were awesome though. It was also interesting the Toulouse Lautrec one. I enjoyed both of them.

I had a splendid day at the museum - used my Barcelona library card and got a discounted entrance fee! The lady at the booth was very kind and explained that I could come back again with the same ticket (valid for 1 month after the first visit).  There is plenty to see, and if you wish to take your time and see everything, I'd recommend allocating the day to this visit  - it did take me around six hours, including an hour lunch break at the museum cafe (the quiche was delicious!), but again, I was taking it slow and stopping to sit down a lot, so it may be shorter for you. TIP: Keep your ticket until the end, as it will be requested by security when entering each new wing/section of the museum :)

One of the best place in the city, for sure! It has so many Catalan arts that one day doesn’t look enough time to provide a throughout visit. Both the museum and nearby area are beautiful. It offers great views of the beauty Barcelona. I suggest visiting it with the others Montjuic attractions. It is specially good to enjoy the sunset from the huge stairs. By the end of the day go downstairs to watch the font magic show!!

Confession: I’m not a fan of art galleries because I don’t know what I’m looking at most of the time. 

I truly enjoyed this gallery; they did a wonderful job of laying everything out in an organized manner. The exhibits are divided into four sections: medieval, gothic, renaissance and modern art.

We opted for the audio tour and went in chronological order. The audio tour was immensely helpful and very well put together as it provided overviews of connecting themes and styles, detailed explanations of the artwork itself, and historical and cultural context. 

If you don’t want to go inside the gallery, exploring the surrounding area is worth a visit. The exterior of the building is gorgeous and sits atop a hill with a giant fountain with a water show at night on the weekends. There’s many places to sit and enjoy the wonderful view of Barcelona!

I would suggest you try arrange to go there Saturday afternoon from 15-18, then it’s free. It’s a nice place with a lot of space also for kids activities. Seems to me a more local activity place. 
Great location and view btw, so really a good walk downstairs towards the magic fountain and the gates and square

This is a top class museum, with an impressive collection that is presented beautifully. The building itself, with views of the city, is well worth visiting but the museum is very special with things worth seeing from across the ages. It doesn't have to take as long to visit as some seem to suggest..

Poble Espanyol, a village that brings together in the form of a real country, the typical places of Spain and the different representations of the art of its regions. In Poble there are 117 buildings, streets and squares within a harmonious composition and global. Without cars but surrounded by the Montjuïc mountain, a visit to the Poble Espanyol is an unusual journey away from traffic, without the noise of the city, with clean air and an extraordinary climate, surrounded by enchanting and suggestive landscapes

My comment is about the having the space at the back for social activities, I find it spacious, well managed, and perfectly located. I attended an event of ~1000 attendees and we had great time is such a nice place

We were here in early March, and most of the shops were closed. Sad. I expected the full experience, but really, it felt more deserted than busy/party/fiesta. I wish places like these had reduced prices for off-season visits, because you're not getting the full experience at all.
Anyway, we checked a few stores, watched the Fiesta presentation (it was cool), walked around, admired some of the architecture, and walked out.

It brings all the Spanish culture together, and you can see one of a kind buildings in one place. I recommend the audio guide. It is superb. The museum is free and has one of a kind Picasso pottery collection!
We had a nice afternoon. Architecture is authentic. Regard you have to invest time for it. Disadvantage: prices and food quality are typical for touristic places.

Beautiful park with great views. Very picturesque and great for kids to run around the only downside is there needs to be a lot more seating especially because there is a lot of walking to get to the top the cafe area had very limited tables and benches and people take up tables and seats they don’t need, bins were overflowing and needed to be cleared out as it was attracting a lot of flies where people were eating which was quite off putting to be honest
Great place to visit if you are walking from the Montjuic Castle.
a very beautiful gardens and spectacular view over Barcelona 🙂
Bucket list! Once in a lifetime
A wonderful location with amazing views. Quiet and a feel of 'off the beaten track". Taken the Montjuic funicular to explore the castle area, and walked down via tranquil beauty.

Cable car is well run and clean but doesn't last very long for the money. The panoramic views from the top are very good and the walk around the castle is nice. The only toilets at the top that we could see were in the castle which means you have to pay to go in first. Bit of tourist rip off if you just wanted to see the views. Would probably walk up next time as looks like a nice walk anyway.

Cable car service: Slightly overpriced for what you get but it's a good experience if you haven't used cable car. 

Castle is rather good but also has an entry cost which is very reasonable. 

Overall nice place to visit with good views of city.
Great views with a smooth ride. Enjoyment as a mode of transport or as a tourist attraction.  Look forward to riding again.
An easy way to to Montjuic Castle. Great views..! A but pricey (about 8€ one way & 12€ with return).

A bit pricey even for a one way ride (8.60 Euro 0r 12.70 two way) but for the experience it was worth the price. I was never on a funicular before so for me it was a special moment. The views are terrific and it takes you right up to the castle which is also accessible by bus. I would highly recommend to take this at least once 😉

We loved everything, tapas with fish were amazing. Good beers. Staff very kind. Location so pretty. Highly recommended
Self-service. Cheap and tasty food. Great for vegetarians!! 1 euro or 1.50 euros per item. But, have to pay together. Not separately
Nice English speaking staff. Good food and atmosphere.

Highly recommend. The waiter is nice and the tapas van be heated if you ask for it. There're many varieties using fish, meat, salmon, fries, avocados...you can find everything! The tapas is 1€ or about 1.5-1.8€. I went there at 15:30, and since it was almost closing time, there weren't many people.
Different kinds of tasty pinchos for good price! It is a small place so it gets crowded easily.
Lovely place with really good food. Pretty good beers and friendly staff. It is a good spot
Incredible food all around. The smoked sardines were really amazing. The eggplant tasted like nothing I’ve ever tasted before. The octopus and the tartare were excellent.
Best pintxos on Blai! Really nice, hearty tapas too.
Cosy place with good food. The excellent service made a difference. Would definitely come back again.
I'm not a big fan of Spanish tortilla but this one a could say it is the best I have ever tried. The pinchos are fresh and creative. The waiters are super nice. It is one of the best of calle Blai

Delicious tapas! Staff is friendly and prices are fantastic. Cheap beer and delicious sangria. They have a "tapa bar" that lets you simply load up a plate and pay per piece. Really easy to get the hang of. Ask the staff what their favourites are.
AMAZING FOOD. Amazing customer service. The best we had in Barcelona during our 5 days stay. We visited the place twice and both of the times we got served by Brian. Amazing guy and very helpful.

INCREDIBLE!!! 
I have been looking for a proper tapas bar and I found one. Great atmosphere where the traditional way of tapas is served. Very authentic and cozy with great music too. 
Food also very tasty for it's reasonable prices. By far my favorite tapas bar here in Barcelona so far... highly recommendable.
Very good pintxos. There's a nice terrace that is heated on the colder days. Super nice. Friendly staff and great food and  tapas. Definitely worth a visit 👌

Very popular,  fun environment, great food. Pricing is per item,  based on toothpick color, €1 or €1,80. Only complaint is that the food tended to not be hot since it was out waiting to be picked up.  I was there early for dinner, around 1900, so that may have played into it (faster turnover later maybe? )
